item.description:
Invisible Dogs

The leashes were on loan from the current owner of 51 Bergen Street, the factory space where the invisible dog toy was invented in the 1970s. Participants of all ages spread out from Red Hook to Brooklyn Heights, very seriously walking their very silly dogs. Be sure to click "watch in HD"!!!! Edited by Matt Adams: http://www.mattadamsapple.com/ "The Dogs Were Let Out by Whom?" by Tyler Walker: http://myspace.com/tylerichiban This is one of nearly 100 different missions Improv Everywhere has executed over the past eight years in New York City. Others include Frozen Grand Central, the Food Court Musical, and the famous No Pants Subway Ride, to name a few.
